ain. Until its [[Boeing 707#707-320C|707-320C]] is delivered in December the airline is using a 707\u2013331{{sic}} leased from [[Tempair International]]. |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"FI1973-85\">{{cite magazine |title=Airlines updated |magazine=[[Flight International]] |date=19 July 1973 |page=85 |url=http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1973/1973%20-%201940.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/68DXjVu7n?url=http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1973/1973%20-%201940.html |archivedate=6 June 2012 |accessdate=6 June 2012 |quote=Bangladesh Biman opened a weekly service from Dacca to London via Bahrain on June 19, using a 707 leased from a division of Templewood Aviation. |url-status=live |df=dmy }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"FI1973-446\">{{cite magazine |title=World Airline Survey \u2013 Bangladesh Biman |magazine=Flight International |date=22 March 1973 |page=446 |url=http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1973/1973%20-%200748.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6DcYQF1z4?url=http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1973/1973%20-%200748.html |archivedate=12 January 2013 |accessdate=12 January 2013 |url-status=live |df=dmy }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"FI1975-475\">{{cite magazine |title=World airline directory \u2013 Bangladesh Biman (National Airlines of Bangladesh) |magazine=[[Flight International]] |volume=108 |number=3445 |date=20 March 1975 |page=475 |url=http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1975/1975%20-%200539.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LlORtAG2?url=http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1975/1975%20-%200539.html |archivedate=10 December 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"FI1979-1349\">{{cite magazine |title=World Airline Survey \u2013 Bangladesh Biman |magazine=[[Flight International]] |date=28 April 1979 |page=1349 |url=http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1979/1979%20-%201411.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.