buse}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Words coined in the 1840s]]\n[[Category:Crime]]\n[[Category:Criminology]]\n[[Category:Dark triad]]\n[[Category:Personality disorders]]\n[[Category:Forensic psychology]]\n[[Category:Psychopathy| ]]\n", "name_user": "KatherineMpennington", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200ePersonality dimensions)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychopathy"}
{"title_page": "Protest \"Volem acollir\"", "text_new": "{{Infobox event\n| title                    = <!-- Title to display, if other than page name --> \"Volem acollir\"\n| image                    = Manifestacio barcelona volem acollir.jpg\n| image_size               =\n| image_upright            =\n| image_alt                =\n| caption                  = Protest 18-F 2017\n| native_name              = Volem acollir\n| native_name_lang         =\n| english_name             = We want to welcome you\n| time                     =\n| duration                 =\n| date                     = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{start and end dates|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> {{start date|2017|02|17}}\n| venue                    =\n| location                 = Barcelona\n| coordinates              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|region:XXXX_type:event|display=inline,title}} -->\n| also_known_as            =\n| type                     = protest\n| theme                    = refugees\n| cause                    = welcoming refugees\n| first_reporter           =\n| budget                   =\n| patron                   = <!-- or |patrons= -->\n| organisers               = <!-- or |organizers= -->\n| filmed_by                =\n| participants             =\n| outcome                  =\n| casualties1              =\n| casualties2              =\n| casualties3              =\n| reported deaths          =\n| reported injuries        =\n| reported missing         =\n| reported property damage =\n| burial                   =\n| inquiries                =\n| inquest                  =\n| coroner                  =\n| arrests                  =\n| suspects                 =\n| accused                  =\n| convicted                =\n| charges                  =\n| trial                    =\n| verdict                  =\n| convictions              =\n| sentence                 =\n| publication_bans         =\n| litigation               =\n| awards                   =\n| url                      =\n| blank_label              = <!-- or |blank_data= -->\n| blank1_label             = <!-- or |blank1_data= -->\n| blank2_label             = <!-- or |blank2_data= -->\n| website                  = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| notes                    =\n}}\nThe '''protest''' \"'''We want to welcome you'''\" (\u00ab''Volem acollir''\u00bb) was celebrated the 18th of February 2017 in Barcelona.&nbsp;According to the&nbsp;[[Municipal police|Gu\u00e0rdia Urbana]]&nbsp;(the Urban city police) 160,000 people assisted the march, and according to the organizers, the number of people who attended it was around 500,000.<ref name=\"desenes\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://cat.elpais.com/cat/2017/02/18/catalunya/1487428212_810988.html Desenes de milers de persones marxen a Barcelona per l\u2019acollida de refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref> It was convoked by the entity&nbsp;''Casa nostra, casa vostra''&nbsp;(''Our home, your home'') in order to ask the institutions and administrations for a more active role in terms of [[European migrant crisis|refugees and migrants in Europe]]. The intention of the entity was for it to be the most multitudinary protest in Europe and they achieved the goal.<ref name=\"protagonitza\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.naciodigital.cat/noticia/125692/barcelona/protagonitza/manifestacio/massiva/europa/refugiats Barcelona protagonitza la manifestaci\u00f3 m\u00e9s massiva d'Europa per als refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref> The same day of the protest, 70,000 people and 900 entities were added to the&nbsp;''Casa nostra, casa vostra'' manifest.<ref name=\"campanyavilaweb\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.vilaweb.cat/noticies/la-campanya-volem-acollir-espera-que-la-manifestacio-pels-refugiats-davui-a-barcelona-sigui-multitudinaria/ La campanya \u2018Volem acollir\u2019 espera que la manifestaci\u00f3 pels refugiats d\u2019avui a Barcelona sigui multitudin\u00e0ria]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nDays before the protest, a concert was held in the [[Palau Sant Jordi]] in Barcelona, with more than 50 artists and 15,000 attended it with the same objective.&nbsp;<ref name=\"ragucci\">Ragucci, Flor&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.publico.es/public/palau-sant-jordi-ple-demana.html Un Palau Sant Jordi ple demana el seu dret a acollir]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref> During the concert, Jordi \u00c9vole criticized the government's inactivity, and he got replied by Llu\u00eds Llach, a former deputy of the Catalan Parliament, who told him that the government had explored all the possible ways to receive and welcome refugees.&nbsp;<ref name=\"llachevole\">Baquero, Camilo S&#x20;\u00ab[http://cat.elpais.com/cat/2017/02/16/catalunya/1487244773_653078.html Llu\u00eds Llach diu que la Generalitat va intentar portar refugiats amb vaixell a Catalunya]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>&nbsp;Days before that a hundred of Catalan mayors had made a call for people to attend the protest.<ref name=\"listaparalamani\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.elperiodico.com/es/noticias/sociedad/barcelona-lista-para-gran-marcha-por-los-refugiados-5845001 Barcelona, lista para la gran manifestaci\u00f3n por los refugiados]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>\n\nThe same day, an article published by the coordinator of the organizer entity, Ruben Wagensberg; the president of&nbsp;[[\u00d2mnium Cultural]], Jordi Cuixart, and the founder of&nbsp;[[Proactiva Open Arms]], \u00d2scar Camps, criticized that \"At the end of 2016, the Spanish State had only received 898 refugees, when it had agreed to welcome more than 17,000\", and it stipulated that it was everyone's responsibility; that anyone could do more, encouraging people to attend the march in order for it to be a \"historical referent for ourselves, and also to develop similar movements all around Europe\".<ref name=\"lluita17\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.naciodigital.cat/noticia/125672/opinio/lluita/compartida/jordi/cuixart/oscar/camps/ruben/wagensberg \u00abUna lluita compartida\u00bb, per Jordi Cuixart, \u00d2scar Camps i Ruben Wagensberg]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>\n\n== Description ==\n[[File:Barcelona_volem_acollir_18-F.jpg|thumb|The protest of 18-F.]]\nThe march started at 4 pm in the [[Pla\u00e7a Urquinaona]]. The route consisted on passing through&nbsp;[[Via Laietana, Barcelona|Via Laietana]]&nbsp;and the &nbsp;Parc de la Barceloneta&nbsp;to get to the&nbsp;Passeig Mar\u00edtim, but the affluence of people provoked that, when people arrived at the end of the way, there were still people trying to move along in the pla\u00e7a Urquinaona.<ref name=\"excusesnd\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.naciodigital.cat/noticia/125686/prou/excuses/acollim/ara/manifestacio/multitudinaria/barcelona/defensa/dels/refugiats \u00abProu excuses!]</ref>\n\nThe mobilization had three headers. The first one with the motto \"''Stop excuses. We welcome now!''\" &nbsp;(\"Prou excuses. Acollim ara!\") was formed by refugees, immigrants and voluntary people. The second one followed the motto \"''No more deaths. Open the borders!''\" (\"No m\u00e9s morts. Obrim fronteres!\"), with the entities that worked in helping the refugees. The third one was composed by entities of the civil society and its motto was \"''Catalonia, land of reception''\" (\"Catalunya, terra d'acollida\").<ref name=\"ccmapersones\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.ccma.cat/324/milers-de-persones-surten-al-carrer-en-la-marxa-volem-acollir-a-favor-dels-refugiats/noticia/2773815/ Milers de persones surten al carrer en la marxa \"Volem acollir\" a favor dels refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;''324.cat'',&#x20;18-02-2017&#x20;[Consulta: 19 febrer 2017].</ref>\n\nThe president of the Catalan Parliament, six government counsellors, the Barcelona's mayoress and numerous deputies of the Congress and the Catalan Parliament assisted the protest.&nbsp;<ref name=\"volemnacion\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.naciodigital.cat/noticia/125664/volem/acollir/barcelona/lidera/clam/europeu/defensa/dels/refugiats/amb/gran/manifestacio \u00abVolem acollir\u00bb: Barcelona lidera el clam europeu en defensa dels refugiats amb una gran manifestaci\u00f3]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>&nbsp;Representatives of all the Catalan formations gave support to the initiative (with the exception of the Partit Popular), as well as social entities, trade unions, ONGs and the Barcelona's archbishopric. At the end of the act, the president of the Generalitat received the organizers at the Palau de la Generalitat.&nbsp;\n\nIn the last speeches, the reception policies of the states were criticized and they demanded changes.&nbsp;Ruben Wagensbert, the spokesman of the organizing entity, demanded in the closing act that they should stop spending public money in fences and that the [[European Union]] should sanction Spain for breaching the reception compromises. He also claimed for a common front of administrations and entities so as to face the wave of fascism in Europe. The Bosnian refugee&nbsp;Dara Ljubojevic and the Syrian Meere M. Zaroor also spoke in the stage. In the evening,&nbsp;[[la Fura dels Baus]]&nbsp;and&nbsp;[[Proactiva Open Arms]] made a representation of a rescue.<ref name=\"lasalas\">Lasalas, Marta&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.elnacional.cat/ca/politica/barcelona-capital-mundial-dels-refugiats_138483_102.html Barcelona, capital mundial dels refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref><ref>Agence France-Presse&#x20;\u00ab[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/feb/18/protesters-in-barcelona-urge-spain-to-take-in-more-refugees?CMP=share_btn_tw Protesters in Barcelona urge Spain to take in more refugees]\u00bb&#x20;(en angl\u00e8s).&#x20;</ref>\n\nAfter the march, the president of the Generalitat,&nbsp;[[Carles Puigdemont]], received the organizers, Ruben Wagensberg and Lara Costafreda, who proposed to make a social pact against racism and xenophobia.<ref name=\"casanostra\">ACN&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.vilaweb.cat/noticies/casa-nostra-casa-vostra-planteja-a-puigdemont-un-pacte-social-contra-el-racisme-i-la-xenofobia-2/ \u2018Casa nostra, casa vostra\u2019 proposa a Puigdemont un pacte social contra el racisme i la xenof\u00f2bia]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>&nbsp;The same day Puigdemont had sent a letter to the European Immigration, Interior and Citizenship commissioner,&nbsp;Dimitris Avramopoulos, to show Catalonia's availability to receive refugees and explain that there were many entities that were preparing to welcome up to 4,500 refugees. The same day, the vicepresident of the Spanish government, [[Soraya S\u00e1enz de Santamar\u00eda]], criticized that Catalonia was willing to take the initiative: \"an autonomos community wants to be the solution to the problem, and it can not be like that\".<ref name=\"arapuigdemont\">Soro, S.&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.ara.cat/societat/Puigdemont-proposa-Brusselles-Catalunya-refugiats_0_1542445887.html Puigdemont proposa a Brussel\u00b7les que Catalunya aculli 4.500 refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>\n\nThere were replicas of the concentration. Mallorca added to the campaign with a march convoked by the Moviment Escolta i Guiatge de Mallorca, where thousands of people participated in going from the Pla\u00e7a Major to the Passeig del Born, where a manifest was read. Dozens of people of the&nbsp;Alta Ribagor\u00e7a got together in front of the Romanesque church [[Sant Climent, Ta\u00fcll|Sant Climent de Ta\u00fcll]]&nbsp;to show support to the campaign.\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:2017 in Catalonia]]\n[[Category:2010s in Barcelona]]\n[[Category:February 2017 events in Spain]]\n[[Category:European migrant crisis]]\n[[Category:2017 protests]]\n[[Category:Protests in Catalonia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox event\n| title                    = <!-- Title to display, if other than page name --> \"Volem acollir\"\n| image                    = Manifestacio barcelona volem acollir.jpg\n| image_size               =\n| image_upright            =\n| image_alt                =\n| caption                  = Protest 18-F 2017\n| native_name              = Volem acollir\n| native_name_lang         =\n| english_name             = We want to welcome you\n| time                     =\n| duration                 =\n| date                     = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{start and end dates|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> {{start date|2017|02|17}}\n| venue                    =\n| location                 = Barcelona\n| coordinates              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|region:XXXX_type:event|display=inline,title}} -->\n| also_known_as            =\n| type                     = protest\n| theme                    = refugees\n| cause                    = welcoming refugees\n| first_reporter           =\n| budget                   =\n| patron                   = <!-- or |patrons= -->\n| organisers               = <!-- or |organizers= -->\n| filmed_by                =\n| participants             =\n| outcome                  =\n| casualties1              =\n| casualties2              =\n| casualties3              =\n| reported deaths          =\n| reported injuries        =\n| reported missing         =\n| reported property damage =\n| burial                   =\n| inquiries                =\n| inquest                  =\n| coroner                  =\n| arrests                  =\n| suspects                 =\n| accused                  =\n| convicted                =\n| charges                  =\n| trial                    =\n| verdict                  =\n| convictions              =\n| sentence                 =\n| publication_bans         =\n| litigation               =\n| awards                   =\n| url                      =\n| blank_label              = <!-- or |blank_data= -->\n| blank1_label             = <!-- or |blank1_data= -->\n| blank2_label             = <!-- or |blank2_data= -->\n| website                  = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| notes                    =\n}}\nThe '''protest''' \"'''We want to welcome you'''\" (\u00ab''Volem acollir''\u00bb) was celebrated the 18th of February 2017 in Barcelona.&nbsp;According to the&nbsp;[[Municipal police|Gu\u00e0rdia Urbana]]&nbsp;(the Urban city police) 160,000 people assisted the march, and according to the organizers, the number of people who attended it was around 500,000.<ref name=\"desenes\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://cat.elpais.com/cat/2017/02/18/catalunya/1487428212_810988.html Desenes de milers de persones marxen a Barcelona per l\u2019acollida de refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref> It was convoked by the entity&nbsp;''Casa nostra, casa vostra''&nbsp;(''Our home, your home'') in order to ask the institutions and administrations for a more active role in terms of [[European migrant crisis|refugees and migrants in Europe]]. The intention of the entity was for it to be the most multitudinary protest in Europe and they achieved the goal.&nbsp;<ref name=\"protagonitza\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.naciodigital.cat/noticia/125692/barcelona/protagonitza/manifestacio/massiva/europa/refugiats Barcelona protagonitza la manifestaci\u00f3 m\u00e9s massiva d'Europa per als refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref> The same day of the protest, 70,000 people and 900 entities were added to the&nbsp;''Casa nostra, casa vostra'' manifest.<ref name=\"campanyavilaweb\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.vilaweb.cat/noticies/la-campanya-volem-acollir-espera-que-la-manifestacio-pels-refugiats-davui-a-barcelona-sigui-multitudinaria/ La campanya \u2018Volem acollir\u2019 espera que la manifestaci\u00f3 pels refugiats d\u2019avui a Barcelona sigui multitudin\u00e0ria]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nDays before the protest, a concert was held in the [[Palau Sant Jordi]] in Barcelona, with more than 50 artists and 15,000 attended it with the same objective.&nbsp;<ref name=\"ragucci\">Ragucci, Flor&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.publico.es/public/palau-sant-jordi-ple-demana.html Un Palau Sant Jordi ple demana el seu dret a acollir]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref> During the concert, Jordi \u00c9vole criticized the government's inactivity, and he got replied by Llu\u00eds Llach, a former deputy of the Catalan Parliament, who told him that the government had explored all the possible ways to receive and welcome refugees.&nbsp;<ref name=\"llachevole\">Baquero, Camilo S&#x20;\u00ab[http://cat.elpais.com/cat/2017/02/16/catalunya/1487244773_653078.html Llu\u00eds Llach diu que la Generalitat va intentar portar refugiats amb vaixell a Catalunya]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>&nbsp;Days before that a hundred of Catalan mayors had made a call for people to attend the protest.<ref name=\"listaparalamani\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.elperiodico.com/es/noticias/sociedad/barcelona-lista-para-gran-marcha-por-los-refugiados-5845001 Barcelona, lista para la gran manifestaci\u00f3n por los refugiados]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>\n\nThe same day, an article published by the coordinator of the organizer entity, Ruben Wagensberg; the president of&nbsp;[[\u00d2mnium Cultural]], Jordi Cuixart, and the founder of&nbsp;[[Proactiva Open Arms]], \u00d2scar Camps, criticized that \"At the end of 2016, the Spanish State had only received 898 refugees, when it had agreed to welcome more than 17,000\", and it stipulated that it was everyone's responsibility; that anyone could do more, encouraging people to attend the march in order for it to be a \"historical referent for ourselves, and also to develop similar movements all around Europe\".<ref name=\"lluita17\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.naciodigital.cat/noticia/125672/opinio/lluita/compartida/jordi/cuixart/oscar/camps/ruben/wagensberg \u00abUna lluita compartida\u00bb, per Jordi Cuixart, \u00d2scar Camps i Ruben Wagensberg]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>\n\n== Description ==\n[[File:Barcelona_volem_acollir_18-F.jpg|thumb|The protest of 18-F.]]\nThe march started at 4 pm in the [[Pla\u00e7a Urquinaona]]. The route consisted on passing through&nbsp;[[Via Laietana, Barcelona|Via Laietana]]&nbsp;and the &nbsp;Parc de la Barceloneta&nbsp;to get to the&nbsp;Passeig Mar\u00edtim, but the affluence of people provoked that, when people arrived at the end of the way, there were still people trying to move along in the pla\u00e7a Urquinaona.<ref name=\"excusesnd\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.naciodigital.cat/noticia/125686/prou/excuses/acollim/ara/manifestacio/multitudinaria/barcelona/defensa/dels/refugiats \u00abProu excuses!]</ref>\n\nThe mobilization had three headers. The first one with the motto \"''Stop excuses. We welcome now!''\" &nbsp;(\"Prou excuses. Acollim ara!\") was formed by refugees, immigrants and voluntary people. The second one followed the motto \"''No more deaths. Open the borders!''\" (\"No m\u00e9s morts. Obrim fronteres!\"), with the entities that worked in helping the refugees. The third one was composed by entities of the civil society and its motto was \"''Catalonia, land of reception''\" (\"Catalunya, terra d'acollida\").<ref name=\"ccmapersones\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.ccma.cat/324/milers-de-persones-surten-al-carrer-en-la-marxa-volem-acollir-a-favor-dels-refugiats/noticia/2773815/ Milers de persones surten al carrer en la marxa \"Volem acollir\" a favor dels refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;''324.cat'',&#x20;18-02-2017&#x20;[Consulta: 19 febrer 2017].</ref>\n\nThe president of the Catalan Parliament, six government counsellors, the Barcelona's mayoress and numerous deputies of the Congress and the Catalan Parliament assisted the protest.&nbsp;<ref name=\"volemnacion\">&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.naciodigital.cat/noticia/125664/volem/acollir/barcelona/lidera/clam/europeu/defensa/dels/refugiats/amb/gran/manifestacio \u00abVolem acollir\u00bb: Barcelona lidera el clam europeu en defensa dels refugiats amb una gran manifestaci\u00f3]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>&nbsp;Representatives of all the Catalan formations gave support to the initiative (with the exception of the Partit Popular), as well as social entities, trade unions, ONGs and the Barcelona's archbishopric. At the end of the act, the president of the Generalitat received the organizers at the Palau de la Generalitat.&nbsp;\n\nIn the last speeches, the reception policies of the states were criticized and they demanded changes.&nbsp;Ruben Wagensbert, the spokesman of the organizing entity, demanded in the closing act that they should stop spending public money in fences and that the [[European Union]] should sanction Spain for breaching the reception compromises. He also claimed for a common front of administrations and entities so as to face the wave of fascism in Europe. The Bosnian refugee&nbsp;Dara Ljubojevic and the Syrian Meere M. Zaroor also spoke in the stage. In the evening,&nbsp;[[la Fura dels Baus]]&nbsp;and&nbsp;[[Proactiva Open Arms]] made a representation of a rescue.<ref name=\"lasalas\">Lasalas, Marta&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.elnacional.cat/ca/politica/barcelona-capital-mundial-dels-refugiats_138483_102.html Barcelona, capital mundial dels refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref><ref>Agence France-Presse&#x20;\u00ab[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/feb/18/protesters-in-barcelona-urge-spain-to-take-in-more-refugees?CMP=share_btn_tw Protesters in Barcelona urge Spain to take in more refugees]\u00bb&#x20;(en angl\u00e8s).&#x20;</ref>\n\nAfter the march, the president of the Generalitat,&nbsp;[[Carles Puigdemont]], received the organizers, Ruben Wagensberg and Lara Costafreda, who proposed to make a social pact against racism and xenophobia.<ref name=\"casanostra\">ACN&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.vilaweb.cat/noticies/casa-nostra-casa-vostra-planteja-a-puigdemont-un-pacte-social-contra-el-racisme-i-la-xenofobia-2/ \u2018Casa nostra, casa vostra\u2019 proposa a Puigdemont un pacte social contra el racisme i la xenof\u00f2bia]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>&nbsp;The same day Puigdemont had sent a letter to the European Immigration, Interior and Citizenship commissioner,&nbsp;Dimitris Avramopoulos, to show Catalonia's availability to receive refugees and explain that there were many entities that were preparing to welcome up to 4,500 refugees. The same day, the vicepresident of the Spanish government, [[Soraya S\u00e1enz de Santamar\u00eda]], criticized that Catalonia was willing to take the initiative: \"an autonomos community wants to be the solution to the problem, and it can not be like that\".<ref name=\"arapuigdemont\">Soro, S.&#x20;\u00ab[http://www.ara.cat/societat/Puigdemont-proposa-Brusselles-Catalunya-refugiats_0_1542445887.html Puigdemont proposa a Brussel\u00b7les que Catalunya aculli 4.500 refugiats]\u00bb.&#x20;</ref>\n\nThere were replicas of the concentration. Mallorca added to the campaign with a march convoked by the Moviment Escolta i Guiatge de Mallorca, where thousands of people participated in going from the Pla\u00e7a Major to the Passeig del Born, where a manifest was read. Dozens of people of the&nbsp;Alta Ribagor\u00e7a got together in front of the Romanesque church [[Sant Climent, Ta\u00fcll|Sant Climent de Ta\u00fcll]]&nbsp;to show support to the campaign.\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:2017 in Catalonia]]\n[[Category:2010s in Barcelona]]\n[[Category:February 2017 events in Spain]]\n[[Category:European migrant crisis]]\n[[Category:2017 protests]]\n[[Category:Protests in Catalonia]]\n", "name_user": "Pikamander2", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protest_%22Volem_acollir%22"}
